Czech police arrested one of Syria's Kurds most prominent leaders on an Interpol red notice put out by Turkey, Turkish and Syrian Kurdish officials said Sunday. Salih Muslim is a former co-chair of the Democratic Union Party (PYD), a dominant Kurdish political party in Syria. The PYD is the political wing of the People's Protection Units (YPG), which Ankara considers to be a "terrorist group" with ties to the banned Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) fighting a three-decade-long insurgency against the Turkish state. The YPG is the main force in the US-backed Syrian Democratic Forces (SDF) fighting against the "Islamic State" (IS). A Kurdish official told AP that Muslim was in Prague on Saturday to attend a conference. After a Turkish participant took a photograph, Czech police detained Muslim, following the request by Turkey. Send  Facebook   Twitter   Google+   Whatsapp   
